The paper discusses the use of Deep Q Learning (DQL) and Reinforcement Learning (RL) in a multifactorial optimization framework. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of meta-heuristic optimization and robotics applications (as mentioned in the abstract) suggest that the paper may also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), Systems and Control (cs.SY), and Robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories.
